===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-awesome.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj-more}}

# (''somewhat dated or formal'') Causing [[awe]] or terror.
#: ''The waterfall in the middle of the rainforest was an awesome sight''.
#: ''The tsunami was awesome in its destructive power.''
# (''colloquial'') Excellent, exciting.
#: ''That concert was awesome!''


====Usage notes====
The most direct meaning of "awesome" is "something which inspires awe", but the word is also a common [[Slang|slang expression]] in the [[English language]]. Similar to "[[hip (slang)|hip]]" and "[[cool]]", the term became popular in the [[1980s]] among [[North American]] youth. Its slang usage most likely originated among [[counter culture|counter cultures]] such as [[skater]]s and [[surfer]]s and continued to propogate through the grunge and drug culture of early 1990s Seattle. Slang usage of "awesome" increased again in the early [[21st century]] partially due to [[nostalgia]] for the [[1980s]] and early [[1990s]]. 

